look like-- these

00:07:05.510 --> 00:07:07.080
connected games--

00:07:07.080 --> 00:07:08.510
how they work.

00:07:08.510 --> 00:07:12.730
We're going to talk a lot about
the importance of data.

00:07:12.730 --> 00:07:15.300
And then we're going to move on
to talk a little bit about

00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:17.290
how we industrialize the
learnings that we get from

00:07:17.290 --> 00:07:19.010
this data, and build
tools that help

00:07:19.010 --> 00:07:21.870
us operate our business.

00:07:21.870 --> 00:07:25.530
So "Here Be Monsters" is a
pretty ambitious project.

00:07:25.530 --> 00:07:28.000
It started about a year
and a half ago.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.860
It's a social game, but we're
trying to take it a little bit

00:07:31.860 --> 00:07:37.010
of a step further and give
it a bit of an RPG feel.

00:07:37.010 --> 00:07:40.520
So it's an online MMO, we're
building it for the web, and

00:07:40.520 --> 00:07:43.510
we're also building it for
Android tablets and the iPad.

00:07:43.510 --> 00:07:46.300
So it'll be launching on the
iPad first, and that should

00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:47.640
come in about early September.

00:07:47.640 --> 00:07:48.970
We're really excited about it.

00:07:48.970 --> 00:07:52.850
So when it's out, definitely
check it out.

00:07:52.850 --> 00:07:54.880
So in Here Be Monsters, you've
got an entire world.

00:07:54.880 --> 00:07:57.020
It's an isometric 2D game.

00:07:57.020 --> 00:08:00.770
You've got an entire world that
you can go and explore.

00:08:00.770 --> 00:08:03.580
And currently, I think-- we're
in beta right now-- currently,

00:08:03.580 --> 00:08:08.080
I think there's about 3,000 to
3,500 unique distinct objects

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:10.510
which exist within the game.

00:08:10.510 --> 00:08:13.850
And so I think the point I'm
trying to make here is that

00:08:13.850 --> 00:08:15.460
Here Be Monsters is all about
data, and we're just

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:19.580
constantly pushing new items
that the players can run

00:08:19.580 --> 00:08:21.060
around the world and collect.

00:08:21.060 --> 00:08:24.270
And once they do collect all
these items, they can combine

00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:27.270
them in really interesting
ways to craft bigger and

00:08:27.270 --> 00:08:28.370
better items.

00:08:28.370 --> 00:08:33.049
So a very, very typical
kind of RPG mechanic.

00:08:33.049 --> 00:08:35.400
And why do they want to go
around the world and collect

00:08:35.400 --> 00:08:37.700
all these items and build all
these interesting things?

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:40.580
Well, they do it because they
want to catch monsters.

00:08:40.580 --> 00:08:42.750
And in order to catch monsters,
there's a trapping

00:08:42.750 --> 00:08:43.470
element to the game.

00:08:43.470 --> 00:08:45.570
So you can build really, really
interesting traps.

00:08:45.570 --> 00:08:48.050
You can travel around to the
right parts of the world.

00:08:48.050 --> 00:08:50.660
You can put some bait
in your trap.

00:08:50.660 --> 00:08:53.090
And then periodically, you'll
check your trap, and you're

00:08:53.090 --> 00:08:57.150
hoping that you've caught the
monster that you're after.

